<BaseLayout
  title="RAG Document Assistant Demo - Ahmad Saladin"
  description="Placeholder PoC page for a RAG document assistant demo using sample documents, retrieved context, source-grounded answers, and productionization notes."
  sideBarActiveItemID="pocs"
>
  <article class="prose max-w-3xl">
    <p class="not-prose text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-primary">Guided demo planned</p>
    <h1>RAG Document Assistant Demo</h1>
    <h2>What It Does</h2>
    <p>This PoC will show a document assistant flow with sample document selection, retrieved context, source-grounded answer, and productionization notes.</p>
    <h2>Who It Is For</h2>
    <p>Startups, internal teams, and agencies building document Q&A, knowledge base assistants, or retrieval-backed LLM apps.</p>
    <h2>Demo Status</h2>
    <p>For v0, this is a placeholder or static walkthrough. It is not a live backend demo yet.</p>
    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <p>User -> Frontend -> API -> Retriever -> Vector Store -> LLM -> Source-grounded answer</p>
    <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
    <p>RAG, vector search, Qdrant, FastAPI, Python, LLM APIs, embeddings.</p>
    <h2>Limitations</h2>
    <p>The v0 version does not upload documents, call an LLM, query a vector database, or depend on a hosted model/API.</p>
    <h2>Productionization Plan</h2>
    <p>Production work would add auth, monitoring, retries, error handling, rate limits, retrieval evaluation, scaling, and cost controls.</p>
    <h2>CTA</h2>
    <p>Want to build something like this? <a href="/contact">Contact me</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
